# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  Axiom OS — Environment Variables
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  Axiom OS is client-side first. The bundled AI routes use the
#  `z-ai-web-dev-sdk`, which needs NO API key in this development environment.
#  Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in keys ONLY when you start wiring
#  real external model providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, local-LLM backends, etc.).
#
#  cp .env.example .env.local

# ── External LLM providers (optional — used when you wire real engines) ──────
# These are read server-side only (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix). Each maps to a
# family in the LLM Registry (Settings → LLM Registry / Engines).

# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=
# GROQ_API_KEY=
# MISTRAL_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# ── Local / self-hosted runtimes (optional) ──────────────────────────────────
# Point Engines at these in the Engines page. Leave commented to use defaults.

# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# LM_STUDIO_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1

# ── Workflow engine modules (optional — Modules page) ────────────────────────
# n8n and LangFlow run as separate local services; Axiom OS only needs their URL.

# N8N_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5678
# LANGFLOW_BASE_URL=http://localhost:7860

# ── Runtime ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NODE_ENV is set automatically by Next.js. Port defaults to 3000.

# PORT=3000
